<div><h3>MSPC 3225 - The Information Society </h3>  <p><hr>This course introduces the birth of the information society, or internet age, though a historical </p>

<p>framework and seeks to avoid historical amnesia in addressing contemporary topics in digital </p>

<p>communications. Issues of selfhood, its evolution, and the role of technology in this progression </p>

<p>are examined. The guiding motivations that inform how and why we build the digital world are </p>

<p>also analyzed. Innovations such as the Internet of Things (IoT), augmented reality (AR), and </p>

<p>blockchain are introduced. <br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Varied<br><br></p></div>		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
